You may kill me, <b>but you will not defeat me.</b><br>Silver Daggers</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#871f78><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub15.ezboard.com/uatton.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Atton</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#0000FF>(10/1/01 1:36:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub15.ezboard.com/fdaggersincamelotfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What Realm? </span><hr size=1> First I agree with Doger, I just want to be in the same realm and server as all of you <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  Second I really like your idea Haemish that we pick one server for each realm.  Even though I haven’t played the beta <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , I really see a lot of us wanting to check out the other realms even for a short visit, so it would be nice if you start a character that you know the other Daggers would be starting their characters on that server too.  Personally I would like us to choose one Realm as our MAIN realm.  Meaning that is the realm that we will play the most.  I say this because some of us may only have time to concentrate on one character.  However I wouldn’t object to the plan you just suggested of rotating realms.  The only problem I see is if someone doesn’t have time to keep 3 characters up to a significant level to stay with the group, for the week that realm(s) are up, they would need to sit out.  Which may be acceptable I guess.   I really can find a class to play in any realm so I don’t care too much, if I HAD to pick, right now I would pick the Midgard Hunter.<br>
