<br>
And Dog....woof. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#871f78><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub15.ezboard.com/udraevenarmitage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DraevenArmitage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ezOP</span><br> <font color=#0000FF>(10/1/01 2:02:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub15.ezboard.com/fdaggersincamelotfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: What Realm? </span><hr size=1> Keep in mind, I doubt we'll be choosing a definate realm server combo until a few weeks after release, so on that note, make your first few characters your TEST characters,  don't plan on them being permanant.<br>
<br>
While I don't think Haemish's idea of Rotating realms is a bad one, I just couldn't go along with it.. . I make one character, and I stick with it.. I may make Alts, but I have a primary character and spend 90% of my time on that.<br>
<br>
